Job Desciption

Objective


Manage chemical laboratory and maintain a high level of technical compliance and quality performance for the laboratory of consumable products testing. Optimize the team organization and productivity as well as all aspect of the chemical laboratory operation in a good discipline. Act as technical expert of the Chemical laboratory, responsible in developing/implementing new testing method and regulatory requirements.

Your Responsibilities


Operate the management system and ISO 17025;
Manage and improve operations workflow, processes and resources, to ensure work effectiveness and efficiency in the laboratory;
Develop and implement new testing method and regulatory requirements;
Provide technical advice on new test capability development;
Understand client request/instruction on test requirement(s);
Identify potential issues in the laboratory; analyze and provide timely resolution of technical problems;
Review and approve chemical test methods, SOPs, WIs and datasheets;
Review chemical testing data and approve test report;
Analyze and identify training goals and needs; design and deliver training;
Involve in budget planning
The Skills We’re Looking For

Degree or above in Chemistry related subject, e.g. Chemistry or Analytical Chemistry
At least 5 years management/supervisory experience in chemical testing laboratory operation, including testing result and report review, method validation and measurement uncertainty estimation;
In-depth knowledge of ISO 17025 and accreditations requirement; 
In-depth knowledge of toy, consumer products, or food contact article safety standards/requirements in various countries;
In-depth knowledge of measurement uncertainty estimation and application;
In-depth knowledge of method validation or verification;
Good trouble shooting and supervision, leadership skills; 
Good communication skills and interpersonal relationship skills;
Able to manage the test instrument, e.g. AAS, GC/MS, LC/MS, ICP-OES, ICP-MS, and UV-VIS;
Proficiency in MS Office Suites;
Approval signatory is preferred;
Fluent in written and spoken English and Chinese;
Analytical mind and logical thinking;
Strong technical knowledge.
Other Benefits:

5-day work, public holidays
Performance bonus and year-end bonus
Medical and Dental insurance
Annual Leave, Compensation Leave, Compassionate Leave

Key responsibilities:

Oversee people management of corresponding team, including staffing & resources management,
development and drive the performance culture;
Formulate staff training and people development plan in accordance with business strategy,
company direction and employee's individual needs;
Manage the routine operation and staff resources of corresponding team. Recommending
technical methods, instruments to be us ed and the necessary reagents and consumables required;
Ensure proficiency testing and internal quality control performed in laboratory. Monitoring and
periodic review of SOP of the departments and carrying out test evaluation or quality improvement programs as necessary;
Lead, monitor and control internal quality system and internal audit for the whole laboratory. Ensure compliance to ISO 17025 and all quality standards of the team;
Control and monitor the integrity and confidentiality of information in the test reports in compliance with the code of conduct of the Laboratory;
Investigate and resolve any complaint cases and recommend optimization plans;• Provide professional advices to internal parties on technical and compliance issues, as well as internal process / practices alignment;
Perform other duties / tasks as required.
Requirements:

Degree holder or above in chemistry or any related discipline
Minimum 8 years of relevant experiences and at least 3 years’ laboratory operation and supervisory experience;
Knowledge in HOKLAS laboratory quality system requirement;
Good analytical and problem-solving skills with ability to work independently;
Good management, communication and interpersonal skills;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese including Mandarin;

