Scientific Officer in the Department of Infectious Diseases and Public Health (Appointment for 12 months) [Ref. C/R/384/03]Duties

The appointee will be responsible for coordinating and conducting the STEM Laboratory’s research activities focused on LC-MS based metabolomics in animals, delivering written reports for scientific communication of research findings, and conducting school visits as part of the STEM Laboratory’s outreach activities.  Main duties include to:

Serve as a project manager, providing scientific and technical leadership as well as supervision of research staff concerned;
Perform experiments, draft proposals and manuscripts, mentor students in projects and research;
Assist the core members of the STEM Laboratory in research related matters such as data analysis of LC-MS based metabolomics data, preparation and submission of manuscripts and grant proposals;
Conduct outreach programmes for high-school students interested in STEM curriculum choices;
Organize laboratory meetings, seminars and conferences as needed;
Provide administrative support, such as filing animal ethics approval requests and risk analysis reports as needed;
Conduct off-campus field trips for sample collection as needed; and
Perform any other duties as assigned.
Requirements
A PhD degree in Molecular Biology/Biomedical Sciences/Animal Science/Biochemistry/ Biology or a related discipline, with relevant experience;
Good understanding of LC-MS based metabolomics workflow, confident use of relevant data analysis techniques such as multivariate statistical methods in R, and experience in the biological interpretation of metabolic profile alterations;
Proven track record of success in scientific research (as evidenced by first-authored publications in reputable scientific journals); and
Good command of written and spoken English for science, strong communication and interpersonal skills, ability to work independently, being self-motivated and a good team player.

(Those who have responded to the previous advertisement need not re-apply.)

